article.headline: Indiana State 59, Western Michigan 57
article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. (AP) -- David Moss hit a 14-foot jump shot with 0.6 seconds left, giving Indiana State a 59-57 victory over Western Michigan in an ESPN BracketBuster game Saturday. Moss led Indiana State (12-13) with 17 points and scored five points in the final two minutes. He hit three of five 3-point shots and went 7-for-14 from the field overall. The Sycamores rallied from a 13-point deficit and halted Western Michigan's home-winning streak at five. They led only twice -- 2-0 in the game's opening minute on a basket by Jay Tunnell, and 59-57 at the end. Joe Reitz led the Broncos (11-14) with game highs of 23 points and eight rebounds. It was his eighth consecutive game in double figures. Gabriel Moore scored 10 points for Indiana State. After Western Michigan pulled ahead 44-31 with 15:03 left, the Broncos didn't score a basket for nearly eight minutes and had just one -- an inside layup by Reitz -- in 11 minutes. The Sycamores outscored Western Michigan 18-8 in that stretch and tied the score at 57 on two free throws by Tunnell with 55 seconds remaining. The Broncos outrebounded Indiana State 37-29 but missed all seven of their 3-point shots in the second half and made just eight of 16 free throws in the game. The Sycamores made 13 of 19 free throws and 42 percent (21 of 50) of its shots from the field.
